sec.p:
This project research task aims at:


the analysis of the influence caused by percussion impeller shaft movement on the wearing of the sliding rings;

the analysis of the influence of mineral materials (in slurry or crude oil) on the wearing of the sliding rings.

The performance of a mechanical seal is improved when wear at the sealing surfaces can be eliminated or greatly reduced. The causes of wear at the seal face have been identified as:


impact load;

erosive wear.

The basic test facility task is to:


provide quick sample (rings) exchange;

provide quick and easy definition of mass loss of the sealing sliding rings;

adjust the contact pressure and the sliding ring speed;

find weak spots in the construction of seals.

The new solution has also been tested on the experimental facility. Testing was done only with water with the same working regime as was done in the previous case. For sealing rings, the following pair was applied:ČL4751–ČL4751. By this constructive solution the following has been achieved:


better shaft sealing and reduced erosion wear;

smooth operation of seals, Figure 10, without impact load, because the angular movement, through the casings (14) and (15), is transferred to the sliding rings (12), which adjust its position to the fixed plate (10);

the force of pressure in the fluid provides a non-contact operation of the rings; friction is reduced to a minimum and seal tightness is kept at all operating conditions.

